properties.Name: PolicyholderContactRole
properties.Description:
The person, organization or department that the Policyholder contacts for assistance, information or support regarding the associated Policyholder Role.

Note that organization would be referenced through the department.

The intent of this data structure is to provide a means of answering types of questions such as:

- Who does Policyholder 'x' contact regarding payment questions?
- Where does Policyholder 'y' direct questions regarding claims?

These types of queries are significant components of help desk and Policyholder service applications.

Columns.Name: PolicyholderId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Policyholder.

Columns.Name: ContactRoleId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Contact Role.

Columns.Name: PersonName
Columns.Description: The name of the person performing or fulfilling the associated Policyholder Contact Role person.

Columns.Name: TelephoneNumber
Columns.Description: The telephone number of the person performing the associated Policyholder Contact Role.

Columns.Name: FaxNumber
Columns.Description: The fax number of the person performing the associated Policyholder Contact Role.

Columns.Name: EmailAddress
Columns.Description: The email address of the  person performing the associated Policyholder Contact Role.

Columns.Name: EmployeeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Employee.
